<h3>7. NSS Team &amp; Volunteer Management (nss.py)</h3>
<pre>
@nss_bp.route('/api/add-team', methods=['POST'])
@login_required
def add_team():
    data = request.json
    team = NSSTeam(
        team_name   = data['team_name'],
        team_leader = data['team_leader'],
        location_id = int(data['location_id']) if data['location_id'] else None,
        enabled     = True
    )
    db.session.add(team)
    db.session.commit()
    return jsonify({'message': 'Team added successfully'})

@nss_bp.route('/api/add-volunteer', methods=['POST'])
@login_required
def add_volunteer():
    data = request.json
    volunteer = Volunteer(
        name              = data['name'],
        email             = data['email'],
        phone             = data['phone'],
        team_id           = int(data['team_id']) if data['team_id'] else None,
        joined_date       = parse_date(data['joined_date']),
        contribution_type = data.get('contribution_type'),
        hours_worked      = int(data.get('hours_worked') or 0),
        impact            = data.get('impact')
    )
    db.session.add(volunteer)
    db.session.commit()
    return jsonify({'message': 'Volunteer added successfully'})

@nss_bp.route('/certificate/&lt;int:id&gt;')
@login_required
def generate_certificate(id):
    volunteer = Volunteer.query.get_or_404(id)
    return render_template('certificate.html', volunteer=volunteer)
</pre>
<p class="explanation"><strong>Explanation:</strong> Manages NSS teams and their volunteers. Admins can add, edit, enable/disable, and delete teams. Volunteers are assigned to teams with tracked contributions. A certificate generation feature renders a printable HTML certificate for each volunteer.</p>

<hr>

<h3>8. Event Management (events.py)</h3>
<pre>
@events_bp.route('/api/add-event', methods=['POST'])
@login_required
def add_event():
    data = request.json
    event = Event(
        name        = data['name'],
        event_date  = data['event_date'],
        description = data['description'],
        is_fixed    = False
    )
    db.session.add(event)
    db.session.commit()
    return jsonify({'message': 'Event added successfully'})

@events_bp.route('/events/register/&lt;int:event_id&gt;', methods=['GET', 'POST'])
@login_required
def register_event(event_id):
    event = Event.query.get_or_404(event_id)
    if request.method == 'POST':
        registration = EventRegistration(
            event_id  = event_id,
            name      = request.form['name'],
            email     = request.form['email'],
            phone     = request.form['phone'],
            team_name = request.form['team_name']
        )
        db.session.add(registration)
        db.session.commit()
        return redirect(url_for('events.registration_success', event_id=event_id))
    return render_template('event_register.html', event=event)
</pre>
<p class="explanation"><strong>Explanation:</strong> Handles creation of environmental awareness events and participant registration. Fixed/official events (like World Earth Day) are seeded at startup and cannot be deleted. Custom events can be added and removed by admins.</p>

<hr>

<h3>9. Report Generation with Chart (report.py)</h3>
<pre>
@report_bp.route("/report")
@login_required
@admin_required
def report():
    volunteers = Volunteer.query.all()
    results = db.session.query(
        func.strftime('%Y-%m', WasteRecord.recorded_date).label('month'),
        func.sum(WasteRecord.quantity_kg)
    ).group_by('month').order_by('month').all()
    months = [r[0] for r in results]
    values = [float(r[1]) for r in results]

    # Generate bar chart using Matplotlib
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
    plt.bar(months, values, color="#10b981")
    plt.title("Monthly Waste Collection Performance (kg)")
    plt.savefig("app/static/waste_chart.png")
    plt.close()

    return render_template("report.html", volunteers=volunteers,
                           waste_data=table_waste_data, chart_file="waste_chart.png")
</pre>
<p class="explanation"><strong>Explanation:</strong> Admin-only route that generates a comprehensive management report. It queries monthly waste totals, renders a styled bar chart using Matplotlib, saves it as a static image, and passes volunteer data and chart to the report template.</p>

<hr>

<h3>10. Admin Access Decorator (auth_utils.py)</h3>
<pre>
def admin_required(view_func):
    @wraps(view_func)
    def wrapped_view(*args, **kwargs):
        if current_user.is_admin():
            return view_func(*args, **kwargs)
        message = translate("admin_access_only")
        if request.path.startswith("/api/") or request.is_json:
            return jsonify({"message": message}), 403
        flash(message)
        return redirect(url_for("data.index"))
    return wrapped_view
</pre>
<p class="explanation"><strong>Explanation:</strong> A reusable Python decorator that restricts route access to admin users only. For API calls it returns a 403 JSON error; for page requests it redirects with a flash message. Applied to sensitive routes like the report page.</p>

